Description:
Operating within their full scope of practice, the RN provides patient care and supports delivery of programs by focusing on the identification, provision and management of resources and self-management strategies to improve patient health. The RN provides immunizations, injections, minor procedures and supports patients in treating minor episodic illnesses and injuries and stabilized chronic illnesses. The RN participates in the development, implementation and evaluation of chronic disease prevention and management programs including education, counseling and self-management.
DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:
· Provides services to patients within full scope of practice of a registered nurse by assessing patients’ complete health care needs (physical, emotional, psychological, mental);
· Participates in Summerville’s Chronic Disease Management and Prevention programs – e.g. Heart Health; Smoking Cessation; Diabetes Management, Geriatric Management, Palliative Care;
· Develops and delivers health education and other activities that assist, promote and support patients or communities as they strive to achieve the highest possible level of health;
· Observes and records vital and biometric measurements as well as outcomes;
· Triages patients according to acuity;
· Executes medical directives accordingly and assists with minor procedures
· Performs various clinical procedures such as suture removal, skin and wound dressing, TB testing, wart treatment, ear syringing, etc.;
· Partners and works collaboratively as part of an interdisciplinary team;
· Maintains accurate, concise and confidential EMR documentation;
· Ensures immunization inventory is monitored and ordered regularly;
· Ensures immunizations are current and educates patients as to their need and any possible side effects;
· Maintains the INR monitoring and management system as per guidelines;
· Ensures adequate supplies and equipment are available for daily patient care and emergency situations;
· Sterilizes equipment for minor surgical procedures;
· Completes all appropriate forms as required;
· Other duties as assigned.
Key QUALIFICATIONS AND EDUCATIONAL REQUIREMENTS:
· Bachelor of Science Degree in Nursing Current certificate of Registration from the Ontario College of Nurses;
· Excellent patient assessment and triaging skills;
· A minimum of 2 years working experience in a primary care setting;
· Health promotion skills including population health;
· CPR certification required.
· Excellent written and verbal communication skills, including facilitation skills;
· Intermediate knowledge of Microsoft Word, Excel and EMR (e.g. Accuro);
· Able to work flexible hours in order to meet patient and physician needs which may include evenings.
